Business Brief -- BTU International Inc.:
   Firm to Post Write-Down
   For Sale of Stake in Unit
BTU said it sold an 80.6% stake in the unit to Kokusai
Electric Ltd. of Tokyo for about $12 million. The unit has
been transferred to a new joint venture called Bruce
Technologies International Inc, the company added. BTU owns a
19.4% stake in the venture.
   BTU, which makes equipment used in manufacturing
integrated circuits, said it will account for the sale of the
unit's assets as a discontinued business. The unit has
contributed about 50% of BTU's annual sales.
   Separately, BTU said it refinanced its mortgage debt with
a new $6.8 million mortgage on its headquarters.